<paragraph id="019C01B4BC76C61B42CB0E7329A18099" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9C7C69819FDE4189587F89EFE9E9F089" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176">
<taxonomicName id="AE94232A7D5300422C63E9A3A765681E" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ericameria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ericameria nauseosa" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nauseosa">Ericameria nauseosa</taxonomicName>
was abundant along Cow Dung Road due north of MDRS, in the lowlands between rocky outcrops between MDRS and the Burpee Dinosaur Quarry (Fig. 27). 
<bibRefCitation id="CE4C8E721B7CEA3D1BD6074923C07EAC" author="Welsh, S. L." journalOrPublisher="Print Services, Brigham Young University, Provo" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="A Utah Flora" year="1993">Welsh et al. (1993)</bibRefCitation>
treats this species as 
<taxonomicName id="FBB49B6D524AAD163F9BFE2CF6A1F3D1" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Chrysothamnus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Chrysothamnus nauseous" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nauseous">Chrysothamnus nauseous</taxonomicName>
(Pallas ex Pursh) Britton, with 14 varieties in Utah. Four of these varieties (
<taxonomicName id="3501E02D52B1C7116516BA77C6E6CEE7" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. nauseous var. consimilis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="variety" species="nauseous" variety="consimilis">C. nauseous var. consimilis</taxonomicName>
(Greene) Hall, 
<taxonomicName id="D29189FF546687D53D215ADE5FA7C93F" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. nauseous var. gnaphaloides" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="variety" species="nauseous" variety="gnaphaloides">C. nauseous var. gnaphaloides</taxonomicName>
(Greene) Hall, 
<taxonomicName id="17B253D271CD63B2C133BA3D6E042BCE" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. nauseous var. junceus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="variety" species="nauseous" variety="junceus">C. nauseous var. junceus</taxonomicName>
(Greene) Hall, and 
<taxonomicName id="2CCAC5665F63C11C9E11F85EBC564221" authority="" authorityName="" class="Centricae" family="Chironomidae" genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" infraspecific-rank="var." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="C. nauseous var. leiospermus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" phylum="Diatomeae" rank="variety" species="nauseous" variety="leiospermus">C. nauseous var. leiospermus</taxonomicName>
(Gray) Hall) were previously reported for the nearby San Rafael Swell (
<bibRefCitation id="18C2DC691DC51F162D90BF61F5D09ECA" author="Harris, JG" journalOrPublisher="Great Basin Naturalist" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" pagination="79 - 87" title="A vascular flora of the San Rafael Swell, Utah" volume="43" year="1983">Harris 1983</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="0EE9BE8780777F1B935CDE7DDED00592" author="Urbatshc, LE" editor="Flora of North America Editorial Committee, eds." journalOrPublisher="New York and Oxford" pageId="0" pageNumber="8176" title="Flora of North America North of Mexico" year="2006">Urbatshc et al. (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, whose treatment we follow here, accept 21 varieties in North America; however we were unable to identify our specimen to variety as the diagnostic phyllaries were missing.
</paragraph>
